          "text": "YOU ARE A PROFESSIONAL PHOTO EDITOR, COMPOSITOR, AND FACE RESTORER.\n\nSUBJECTS (Image 1) + BACKGROUND (Image 2) → FINAL COMPOSITE\n\nIDENTITY & FACES:\n- Preserve every subject's facial identity 100% — no warping, \n  blending, or distortion of any face\n- Restore and sharpen faces if needed after compositing\n- Body proportions must remain natural and unchanged\n\nPOSITIONING & GROUNDING:\n- Every subject must be firmly grounded on the floor/ground plane \n  of the background image\n- Match the floor perspective — all subjects share the same ground \n  horizon line\n- Standing subjects: both feet fully flat on the ground, no floating\n- Sitting/floor subjects: full body contact with the ground surface\n- Adjust each subject's vertical position until ground contact is \n  physically convincing\n\nFURNITURE & PROPS:\n- If any subject is seated on furniture (chair, bench, sofa, stool), \n  include that furniture in the final composite\n- Remove any carpets, rugs, or floor coverings from Image 1\n\nSHADOWS & LIGHTING:\n- Analyze the light source direction and quality in Image 2\n- Apply matching shadows beneath every subject's feet and body\n- Shadow softness, length, and direction must be consistent across \n  all subjects and match the background lighting\n- Match skin tones and clothing colors to the ambient light color \n  temperature of Image 2\n\nBLENDING & INTEGRATION:\n- Seamlessly blend subject edges into the background — no harsh \n  cutout lines or halos\n- Match grain, noise, and texture between subjects and background\n- Color grade subjects to match the mood and tones of Image 2\n- No vignette unless naturally present in Image 2\n\nCOMPOSITION:\n- Subjects are the hero — they should be prominent and well-lit\n- Subjects must appear in FRONT of all background elements\n- Maintain original subject poses exactly as they appear in Image 1\n- Accurate scale and perspective relative to the background scene\n\nQUALITY CHECK:\n- No floating subjects\n- No distorted faces or bodies\n- No visible compositing artifacts\n- Photorealistic final result",
